### Key Findings

- **Root cause confirmed**: `RAILWAY_TOKEN` GitHub Actions secret is expired/revoked — the "Validate Railway secrets" step in `.github/workflows/staging-pipeline.yml` (lines 39-54) returns `Not Authorized` from the Railway GraphQL API.
- **Human-only fix**: No code changes needed. Generate a new permanent token at `https://railway.com/account/tokens`, then `gh secret set RAILWAY_TOKEN --repo alexsiri7/reli`.
- **Recurring pattern**: This is the 4th occurrence (prior: #733, #740, #741). Each was fixed identically — the pipeline code is correct; the secret value just goes stale.
- **Prevention gap**: No automated token health check exists. A weekly cron workflow that validates the token could provide early warning before CI breaks.

### Gaps

- Exact Railway token expiry window is undocumented — unclear whether tokens last 30 days, 90 days, or until account changes. Empirically, this happens every few months.
